Subject: [PATCH] Put more stuff in .modinfo section
Date: Sun, 06 Apr 2003 16:29:51 +1000
Message-Id: <20030406063054.CD4262C0B2@lists.samba.org>
Sender: linux-kernel-owner@vger.kernel.org
X-Mailing-List: linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org

Linus, please apply.

Restore the macros for MODULE_AUTHOR, MODULE_DESCRIPTION and
MODULE_PARM_DESC, so they drop strings into .modinfo (as in 2.4).

Also put vermagic and license in that section.  MODULE_ALIAS already
goes there, as does a list of module dependencies generated at build
time (thanks to Kai).

Cheers,
Rusty.
--
  Anyone who quotes me in their sig is an idiot. -- Rusty Russell.

Name: Restore modinfo section
Author: Rusty Russell
Status: Tested on 2.5.66-bk2
Depends: Module/kallsyms-kai-fix.patch.gz

D: Restores .modinfo section, and uses it to store license and vermagic.

